<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 3:08PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Jefferson County
through 400 PM CDT...
At 308 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sugden, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Waurika, Ringling, Ryan, Sugden and Cornish.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
